# UI and Styling

- Use Uniwind (Tailwind CSS for React Native) via `className` prop — never inline `style` for colors, spacing, or layout
- Always support dark mode: pair light classes with `dark:` variants
- Use semantic theme tokens from `global.css`: `bg-background dark:bg-dark-background`, `text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary`
- Use `useTheme()` hook from `@/hooks/useTheme` only when dynamic style objects are unavoidable
- Reusable UI components live in `src/components/ui/` (Button, Card, Container, Badge)
- Wallet-specific components live in `src/components/wallet/`
- Screen containers should use the `<Container safe>` component for SafeAreaView + themed background
- Spacing scale: `xs(4) sm(8) md(16) lg(24) xl(32) 2xl(48)` — use Tailwind classes (`p-4`, `mb-6`, etc.)
- Border radius: `rounded-sm(8) rounded-md(12) rounded-lg(16) rounded-xl(24) rounded-full`

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
<View className="bg-surface dark:bg-dark-surface p-4 rounded-lg">
  <Text className="text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary text-base">Hello</Text>
</View>

// ❌ BAD
<View style={{ backgroundColor: '#f8fafc', padding: 16, borderRadius: 12 }}>
  <Text style={{ color: '#0f172a', fontSize: 16 }}>Hello</Text>
</View>
```
